<Docs title="Creating Domains">
  <h1>Creating Domains</h1>

  <p>
    Domains are optional overlays that add industry-specific vocabulary, agent enhancements,
    and guardrails to any profile. They enhance &mdash; never replace &mdash; the base agent config.
  </p>

  <h2>Scaffold a Domain</h2>
  <pre><code>aos create domain my-industry</code></pre>

  <h2>Domain Structure</h2>
  <pre><code>core/domains/my-industry/
  domain.yaml     # Lexicon, overlays, guardrails</code></pre>

  <h2>domain.yaml Schema</h2>
  <pre><code>schema: aos/domain/v1
id: my-industry
name: My Industry
description: "Domain overlay for my industry."

lexicon:
  metrics:
    - "key_metric_1"
    - "key_metric_2"
  frameworks:
    - "industry_framework_1"
  stages:
    - "stage_1"
    - "stage_2"

overlays:
  catalyst:
    lens_additions:
      - label: Industry Revenue Metric
        instruction: "For every opportunity, quantify in terms of key_metric_1."
    evidence_standard: "Revenue claims must include industry-standard benchmarks."

  sentinel:
    lens_additions:
      - label: Compliance Check
        instruction: "Every proposal must address regulatory_requirement."
    evidence_standard: "Risk claims must reference specific regulations."

guardrails:
  - "Regulatory compliance status must be stated explicitly."
  - "Industry-standard metrics must be used in all quantitative claims."</code></pre>

  <h2>How Domains Work</h2>

  <h3>Lexicon</h3>
  <p>Industry-specific vocabulary. Metrics, frameworks, and stages that agents should reference when analyzing problems in this domain.</p>

  <h3>Overlays</h3>
  <p>Per-agent enhancements. Each overlay adds lens additions (new analytical perspectives) and evidence standards specific to the domain. Overlays are merged into agents at runtime &mdash; they append, never replace.</p>

  <h3>Guardrails</h3>
  <p>Domain-wide rules that all agents must follow. These are injected into agent prompts as additional constraints.</p>

  <h2>Using Domains</h2>
  <pre><code>aos run strategic-council --domain my-industry --brief brief.md</code></pre>
  <p>The domain overlay is applied to all agents before the deliberation starts.</p>
</Docs>
